+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++Basic Phrases
はい Hai = Yes,
いいえ Iie(E-Ay) = No,
おねがいします O-negai Shimasu = Please,
ありがとう Arigato = Thank You,
ありがとうございます arigatou gozaimasu = Thank you(polite),
どういたしまして Dotashimaste = You're Welcome,
Owari Da = It's Over, 
すみません SumiMasen = Excuse me,
ごめんなさい GomenNasai = I am sorry,
おはようございます OHayO GozAiMasu = Good Morning,
こんばんは KonBanWa = Good Evening,
おやすみなさい O-Yasumi Nasai = Good Night,

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++Meeting and Greeting
えいごをはなせますか Eigo o hanasemasu ka = Do you speak English?,
ここに　えいごおはなせるひとはいますか Koko ni eigo o hanaseru hito wa imasu ka =  Does anyone here speak English?,
わたしは　にほんごがすこししか　はなせません Watashi wa nihongo ga sukoshi shika hanasemasen = I only speak a little Japanese,
おなまえはなんですか O-namae wa nan desu ka = What is your name?,
わたしのなまえは　かおりです Watashi no namae wa Kaori desu = My name is Kaorii,
おげんきですか O-genki desu ka = How are you?,
げんきです Genki desu = I'm fine. Thank you.,
おあいできて　うれしいです Oaidekite ureshī desu = I am very glad to meet you.,
わかりません Wakarimasen = I don't understand.,
なんていいましたか Nante iimashita ka = What did you say?,
もっと　ゆっくりはなしてください Motto yukkuri hanashite kudasai = Can you speak more slowly?,
よくわかります Yoku wakarimasu = I understand you perfectly.,
ありがとう = Casual Language
ありがとうございます = Polite Language
LastName + ーさん(suffix) or lastname+ jobtitle(polite if you work together)

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++Misc
じ = Gee
木 = Ki = Tree
き = Ki = Yellow
青 = ao = blue
丸 = maru = circle

私 (わたし) = Watashi = I(polite)
これ = ko re = this
それ = so re = that
あれ = a re = that over there

よ = yo Vs ですよ(polite) = evening
ね = ne Vs ですね(polite) = root 
ぜ = ze Vs ます Vs ですよね Vs ましょう (Depends on context)
ぞ = zo
だろう(masculine) Vs です or でしょう (neutral)
かしら(feminine) Vs かもしれない (Polite)
あなた(offensive) = you
運転手 = bus driver
牛乳パック = milk carton
喉が痛い = to have a sore throat
皿を洗う = to wash the dishes
電気を消す = to turn on the lights
コンセントに差す = to plug in
腐敗 = FuHai = Decay
気晴らし = a distraction
決断 = a decision
冷蔵庫 = refrigerator
ドア = door
冷蔵庫のドア = refrigerator door
開く = to open
りんご = apple
落ちた = fell
リンゴが落ちた  = the apple fell
